<paragraph blockId="5.[140,1107,1132,1194]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading bold="true" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Biogeographic notes on the unwinged 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1838" box="[659,799,1132,1159]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[659,799,1132,1159]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Philorhizus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species from the West Palaearctic realm
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[140,1108,1222,1672]" lastBlockId="6.[140,1108,1152,1672]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName authority="Wrase &amp; Assmann, 2008" authorityName="Wrase &amp; Assmann" authorityYear="2008" box="[140,367,1222,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marggii" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[140,367,1222,1248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Philorhizus marggii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[378,445,1223,1249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to a group of species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1838" box="[978,1108,1222,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[978,1108,1222,1248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Philorhizus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is characterized by microptery (or brachyptery) and by the fact of its distribution in mountainous regions. As far as is known at present, these species occur in the western part of the Palaearctic realm from the Macaronesian Islands (Canary Islands, Madeira), the Iberian, Apennine and southern Balkan Peninsulas, up to the Caucasus. The northern limit is marked by populations in the 
<collectingCountry box="[1004,1103,1398,1424]" name="Ukraine" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, the southern by those in the Sierra Nevada, northern Sicily, 
<collectingCountry box="[883,965,1434,1460]" name="Turkey" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and by the population(s) of 
<taxonomicName authority="Wrase &amp; Assmann, 2008" authorityName="Wrase &amp; Assmann" authorityYear="2008" box="[341,476,1469,1495]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marggii" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[341,476,1469,1495]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ph. marggii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[485,550,1469,1495]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[738,819,1469,1495]" name="Greece" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Greece</collectingCountry>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sciaky R" box="[875,1024,1469,1495]" journalOrPublisher="Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="53 - 78" part="1990" refId="ref3823" refString="Sciaky R (1991) Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa. Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69 [1990]: 53 - 78." title="Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa" type="journal article" year="1991">Sciaky 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wrase DW" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitrage" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="807 - 813" part="37" refId="ref3956" refString="Wrase DW (2005) Description of a new Philorhizus species from Greece and faunistic notes on other species previously described (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Lebiini). Linzer biologische Beitrage 37 (1): 807 - 813." title="Description of a new Philorhizus species from Greece and faunistic notes on other species previously described (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Lebiini)" type="journal article" year="2005">Wrase 2005</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Anichtchenko, 2005" authorityName="Anichtchenko" authorityYear="2005" box="[230,712,1504,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tinauti">
<emphasis box="[230,450,1504,1530]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Philorhizus tinauti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Anichtchenko A" box="[462,712,1504,1531]" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la SAE" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="46 - 50" part="12" refId="ref3562" refString="Anichtchenko A (2005) Especies nuevas y poco conocidas de Philorhizus Hope, 1838 (Coleoptera, Carabidae) de Espana. Boletin de la SAE 12: 46 - 50." title="Especies nuevas y poco conocidas de Philorhizus Hope, 1838 (Coleoptera, Carabidae) de Espana" type="journal article" year="2005">Anichtchenko, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a sister species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mateu et Colas, 1954" authorityName="Mateu et Colas" authorityYear="1954" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mendizabali">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ph. mendizabali</emphasis>
Mateu et Colas, 1954
</taxonomicName>
), is known from low altitudes in eastern Andalucia (Almería, 
<bibRefCitation author="Anichtchenko A" box="[262,505,1574,1601]" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la SAE" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="46 - 50" part="12" refId="ref3562" refString="Anichtchenko A (2005) Especies nuevas y poco conocidas de Philorhizus Hope, 1838 (Coleoptera, Carabidae) de Espana. Boletin de la SAE 12: 46 - 50." title="Especies nuevas y poco conocidas de Philorhizus Hope, 1838 (Coleoptera, Carabidae) de Espana" type="journal article" year="2005">Anichtchenko 2005</bibRefCitation>
). At least most, if not all, of these species live in southern glacial refuge areas of the western Palaearctic. Distribution pattern and low power of dispersal resulting from microptery (or brachyptery) in combination with small body size suggest that these taxa survived the glacial periods within or close to the recent/present-day distribution areas (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Holdhaus K" box="[776,967,1187,1214]" journalOrPublisher="Abhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 493" part="13" refId="ref3747" refString="Holdhaus K (1954) Die Spuren der Eiszeit in der Tierwelt Europas. Abhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 13: 1 - 493." title="Die Spuren der Eiszeit in der Tierwelt Europas" type="journal article" year="1954">Holdhaus 1954</bibRefCitation>
). Moreover, we believe that these endemic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1838" box="[500,630,1222,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[500,630,1222,1248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Philorhizus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are relicts because in many cases not only one, but several massifs are colonized (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Habel J &amp; Assmann T" box="[773,1095,1258,1284]" journalOrPublisher="Heidelberg and other: Springer" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refId="ref3721" refString="Habel J, Assmann T (2008) Relict species - phylogeography and conservation biology. Heidelberg and other: Springer (in press)." title="Relict species - phylogeography and conservation biology" type="book" year="2008">Habel and Assmann 2008</bibRefCitation>
). In contrast to some extreme endemics, such as numerous 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Clairville" authorityYear="1806" box="[838,923,1293,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[838,923,1293,1319]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Trechus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species or cave dwelling carabids, it is highly probable that these 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1838" box="[739,869,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[739,869,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Philorhizus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species had a wider distribution in the past. Otherwise it is difficult to explain the existence of some isolated populations of the same species such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Sciaky, 1991" authorityName="Sciaky" authorityYear="1991" box="[725,1017,1398,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dacicus">
<emphasis box="[725,855,1398,1424]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ph. dacicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sciaky R" box="[865,1017,1398,1425]" journalOrPublisher="Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="53 - 78" part="1990" refId="ref3823" refString="Sciaky R (1991) Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa. Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69 [1990]: 53 - 78." title="Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa" type="journal article" year="1991">Sciaky, 1991</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
known from 
<collectingCountry box="[206,313,1434,1460]" name="Romania" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Romania</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[373,469,1434,1460]" name="Ukraine" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kabak I" box="[485,635,1434,1460]" editor="Lobl I, Smetana A" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup (Denmark)" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="408 - 439" refId="ref3622" refString="Kabak I (2003) Tribe Lebiini Bonelli, 1810. In: Lobl I, Smetana A (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera, Volume 1: Archostemata, Myxophaga, Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup (Denmark), 408 - 439." title="Tribe Lebiini Bonelli, 1810." type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera, Volume 1: Archostemata, Myxophaga, Adephaga" year="2003">Kabak 2003</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Sciaky, 1991" authorityName="Sciaky" authorityYear="1991" box="[658,997,1434,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandmayri">
<emphasis box="[658,839,1434,1460]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ph. brandmayri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sciaky R" box="[847,997,1434,1460]" journalOrPublisher="Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="53 - 78" part="1990" refId="ref3823" refString="Sciaky R (1991) Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa. Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69 [1990]: 53 - 78." title="Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa" type="journal article" year="1991">Sciaky, 1991</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
recorded from Sicily and the Aspromonte Mountains in Calabria and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wrase, 1995" authorityName="Wrase" authorityYear="1995" box="[846,1107,1469,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulo">
<emphasis box="[846,955,1469,1495]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ph. paulo</emphasis>
Wrase, 1995
</taxonomicName>
distributed in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[418,484,1504,1530]" name="Spain" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Spain</collectingCountry>
and the Pyrenees. A new record from a locality in the East Pyrenees, about 5 kilometres southwest from Prades-de-Mollo-la-Preste, close to the Spanish border, enlarges the known distribution area of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wrase" authorityYear="1995" box="[882,992,1574,1600]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulo">
<emphasis box="[882,992,1574,1600]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ph. paulo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[186,265,1610,1636]" name="France" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">France</collectingCountry>
(first record for 
<collectingCountry box="[461,544,1610,1636]" name="France" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">France</collectingCountry>
: “ 
<collectingCountry box="[565,649,1610,1636]" name="France" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">France</collectingCountry>
, Collado de Ares, 
<date box="[866,993,1610,1636]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1978-05-27">27.V.1978</date>
, Hozman lgt.” (Dept. Pyrénnées-Orientales); 
<specimenCount box="[561,640,1645,1671]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="male">1 male</specimenCount>
in cWR).
</paragraph>
